{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Take advantage of custom decoding and encoding logic for the shared file storage persistence"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"strategy, as well as beta support for Swift’s native Testing framework.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"title":"Migrating to 1.12","role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library introduced 1 new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API, as well as beta support for Swift Testing."}]},{"style":"important","name":"Important","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tools of version 1.11. See "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for more information."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"anchor":"Custom-file-storage-coding","type":"heading","text":"Custom file storage coding","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.10 of the Composable Architecture introduced a powerful tool for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"overridingTitle":"sharing state","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"sharing state","type":"text"}],"isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" amongst your features, and included several built-in persistence"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"strategies, including file storage. This strategy, however, was not very flexible, and only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"supported the default JSON encoding and decoding offered by Swift."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In this version, you can now define custom encoding and decoding logic using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decode:encode:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Swift Testing","type":"heading","anchor":"Swift-Testing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 16 and Swift 6 come with a powerful new native testing framework. Existing test targets using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"XCTest can even incrementally adopt the framework and define new tests with Testing. Existing XCTest","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"test "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"helpers"}]},{"text":", however, are not compatible with the new framework, and so test tools like the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Composable Architecture’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore"},{"text":" did not work with it out of the box.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That changes with this version, which seamlessly supports XCTest "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" Swift’s Testing framework."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can now create a test store in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Test"},{"type":"text","text":" and failures will be reported accordingly."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/C